## Chapter 2: Technology Stack

CivicPulse is built with a carefully chosen, production-grade stack. Here is every dependency explained:

### 2.1 Frontend

| Technology | Version | Why It Was Chosen |
|-----------|---------|------------------|
| **Next.js** | 14.2.15 | App Router architecture, built-in SSR/SSG, file-based routing, API routes in the same codebase, and Vercel deployment compatibility. The App Router (not Pages Router) is used throughout. |
| **React** | 18.3.1 | Component model, hooks, context API for state. |
| **TailwindCSS** | 3.4.19 | Utility-first CSS with a custom design system (dark theme, gold accent, status/priority colors). No runtime CSS. |
| **react-hot-toast** | 2.4.1 | Lightweight toast notifications for success/error feedback. |
| **Leaflet + react-leaflet** | 1.9.4 / 4.2.1 | Open-source interactive maps for issue location display. No paid API key required for basic use (unlike Google Maps). |
| **react-leaflet-cluster** | 4.0.0 | Groups nearby map markers into clusters to prevent UI clutter when many issues are in the same area. |
| **Recharts** | 3.7.0 | React charting library for analytics dashboards (bar charts, line graphs, pie charts). |
| **browser-image-compression** | 2.0.2 | Compresses images in the browser before upload, reducing bandwidth and Cloudinary storage costs. |
| **@lottiefiles/react-lottie-player** | 3.6.0 | Renders Lottie JSON animations (used in the hero section of the landing page). |
| **i18next + react-i18next** | 25.x / 16.x | Full internationalization support. The UI can be switched between languages. |
| **i18next-browser-languagedetector** | 8.x | Auto-detects the user's browser language on first visit. |

### 2.2 Backend

| Technology | Version | Why It Was Chosen |
|-----------|---------|------------------|
| **Next.js API Routes** | 14.2.15 | The backend lives in the same codebase (`app/api/`). No separate Express server needed. Each file in `app/api/` is a serverless function. |
| **Node.js** | ≥18.17.0 | Required by Next.js 14. Provides the runtime for all server-side code. |

### 2.3 Database

| Technology | Version | Why It Was Chosen |
|-----------|---------|------------------|
| **MongoDB** | (Atlas or local) | Document database chosen for its flexibility with semi-structured civic data (issues have varying numbers of images, comments, escalation history). Geospatial queries (`$near`, `2dsphere`) are built-in. |
| **Mongoose** | 8.1.0 | ODM (Object Document Mapper) that provides schema validation, middleware hooks (pre-save), instance methods, and static methods on top of MongoDB. |

### 2.4 Authentication

| Technology | Version | Why It Was Chosen |
|-----------|---------|------------------|
| **jsonwebtoken** | 9.0.3 | Signs and verifies JWT tokens on the server side (API routes). |
| **jose** | 6.2.0 | Verifies JWT tokens in the **Edge Runtime** (middleware.js runs at the Edge, which cannot use Node.js-only modules like `jsonwebtoken`). `jose` is a Web Crypto API-based JWT library compatible with Edge. |
| **bcryptjs** | 3.0.3 | Hashes user passwords with bcrypt (10 salt rounds) before storing in MongoDB. Pure JavaScript implementation, no native bindings needed. |

> **Why two JWT libraries?** `jsonwebtoken` requires Node.js runtime and is used in regular API routes. `jose` is used only in `middleware.js` which runs in the Edge Runtime (Vercel's CDN edge nodes). This is a constraint of Next.js Edge Middleware.

### 2.5 File Storage

| Technology | Version | Why It Was Chosen |
|-----------|---------|------------------|
| **Cloudinary** | 2.7.0 | Cloud-based image hosting. Citizens upload up to 3 images per issue. Cloudinary handles storage, CDN delivery, and transformation (thumbnails, etc.). |
| **next-cloudinary** | 6.3.0 | Next.js-specific Cloudinary integration with optimized `<CldImage>` component. |

### 2.6 Email

| Technology | Version | Why It Was Chosen |
|-----------|---------|------------------|
| **Resend** | 6.7.0 | Modern developer-friendly transactional email API. Used for all system emails: submission confirmations, status updates, department alerts, rating requests, and OTP emails. |

### 2.7 AI & Computer Vision

| Technology | Version/Model | Purpose |
|-----------|-------------|---------|
| **Google Gemini** (`@google/generative-ai`) | gemini-1.5-flash | Primary AI for image analysis. Analyzes uploaded photos, verifies authenticity, detects civic issue category, subcategory, and priority. |
| **OpenAI GPT-4o-mini** | (via REST API) | Fallback AI for image analysis if Gemini fails. Also used for text analysis and response generation. |
| **OpenAI GPT-3.5-turbo** | (via REST API) | Text-based analysis: classifies issues by title/description, extracts keywords, performs sentiment analysis. |
| **Roboflow** | (via REST API) | Specialized computer vision for pothole detection. Provides high-confidence object detection on road images. Used as the first-pass detector before Gemini. |

### 2.8 Validation

| Technology | Version | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|---------|
| **Zod** | 3.22.4 | Schema-based validation for all API request bodies. Every POST/PATCH endpoint validates its input against a Zod schema before touching the database. This prevents malformed data from ever reaching MongoDB. |

### 2.9 Scheduling & Automation

| Technology | Version | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|---------|
| **node-cron** | 3.0.3 | Schedules automated background tasks: SLA deadline checks, reminder sending, and issue escalation. |

