## Chapter 5: Database Models

MongoDB stores data in 7 collections, managed by Mongoose schemas.

### 5.1 User Model (`models/User.js`)

The User model covers all 5 roles in a single collection. Role-specific fields are conditionally populated.

```
Collection: users
```

**Fields:**

| Field | Type | Required | Notes |
|-------|------|----------|-------|
| `name` | String | ✅ | Trimmed |
| `email` | String | ✅ | Unique, lowercase, trimmed |
| `password` | String | ✅ | bcrypt hash. `select: false` — never returned by default |
| `phone` | String | ❌ | Optional contact number |
| `role` | String (enum) | ✅ | See role enum below. Default: `CITIZEN` |
| `wardId` | String | ❌ | `ward-1` through `ward-16`. Required for FIELD_OFFICER only |
| `departmentId` | String | ❌ | `roads`, `lighting`, etc. Required for DEPARTMENT_MANAGER |
| `department` | ObjectId → Department | ❌ | Legacy ref to Department collection |
| `googleId` | String | ❌ | For future Google OAuth integration (sparse index) |
| `address.street/city/state/pincode` | String | ❌ | Optional address |
| `isActive` | Boolean | — | Default: `true`. Deactivated users cannot log in |
| `welcomeEmailSent` | Boolean | — | Prevents duplicate welcome emails |
| `otp` | String | ❌ | Password reset OTP |
| `otpExpires` | Date | ❌ | OTP expiry timestamp |
| `createdAt` | Date | — | Auto-set to `Date.now` |

**Role Enum (both legacy and current):**
```javascript
enum: [
  'citizen', 'department', 'municipal', 'admin', 'commissioner', // legacy
  'CITIZEN', 'FIELD_OFFICER', 'DEPARTMENT_MANAGER', 'SYSTEM_ADMIN', 'MUNICIPAL_COMMISSIONER' // current
]
```

**Indexes:**
- `{ phone: 1 }` — sparse (not all users have phones)
- `{ wardId: 1, departmentId: 1 }` — composite for filtering staff by assignment
- `{ role: 1, departmentId: 1 }` — finding all staff in a department
- `{ role: 1, isActive: 1 }` — finding active users by role
- `{ department: 1 }` — legacy department reference lookups
- `{ role: 1 }` — role-based queries

**Pre-save hooks:**
1. **Password hashing** — If `password` is modified, auto-hash with bcrypt before saving
2. **Department field cleanup** — If role is not a department-type role, `department`, `departmentId`, and `wardId` are cleared to `null/undefined`

### 5.2 Issue Model (`models/Issue.js`)

The most complex model. An issue represents a single civic complaint from creation through resolution.

```
Collection: issues
```

**Core Fields:**

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| `reportId` | String | Unique. Auto-generated as `R00001`, `R00002`, etc. Used for public tracking |
| `title` | String | Required. 10–200 characters |
| `description` | String | Required. 30–2000 characters |
| `category` | String (enum) | Required. One of 8 categories |
| `subcategory` | String | Required. Specific sub-type within category |
| `priority` | String (enum) | `low`, `medium`, `high`, `urgent`. Default: `medium` |
| `status` | String (enum) | `pending`, `assigned`, `in-progress`, `resolved`, `rejected`, `reopened`, `escalated` |
| `ward` | String | Required. `ward-1` through `ward-16`. Determines zone + department |

**Location Object:**
```javascript
location: {
  address: String,       // Human-readable address
  coordinates: {
    type: "Point",         // GeoJSON type for geospatial queries
    coordinates: [lng, lat]  // NOTE: MongoDB uses [longitude, latitude] order!
  },
  city: String,
  state: String,
  pincode: String
}
```

> ⚠️ **Important:** MongoDB GeoJSON uses `[longitude, latitude]` order, which is the **reverse** of common conventions like `[lat, lng]`. This must be handled carefully when interfacing with Leaflet which uses `[lat, lng]`.

**AI Detection Fields:**
```javascript
detectionSource: 'roboflow' | 'gemini' | 'openai' | 'keyword' | 'manual' | 'AI_CONFIRMED' | 'AI_OVERRIDDEN'
cvModelResults: Mixed    // Raw AI response stored for auditing
aiAnalysis: {
  category: String,
  priority: String,
  sentiment: String,
  keywords: [String]
}
```

**SLA Object:**
```javascript
sla: {
  deadline: Date,            // Auto-calculated from priority
  hoursRemaining: Number,    // Recalculated on every save
  isOverdue: Boolean,        // true if deadline < now
  escalationLevel: Number,   // 1, 2, or 3
  escalationHistory: [{
    level: Number,
    escalatedAt: Date,
    escalatedTo: String,     // 'Department Staff' | 'Department Head' | 'Commissioner/Mayor'
    reason: String
  }]
}
```

**SLA Deadlines by Priority:**
| Priority | Deadline |
|----------|----------|
| `urgent` | 24 hours |
| `high` | 48 hours |
| `medium` | 72 hours |
| `low` | 120 hours |

**Upvoting:**
```javascript
upvotes: Number,          // Count
upvotedBy: [ObjectId]     // User IDs who upvoted (prevents duplicates)
```

**Feedback/Rating:**
```javascript
feedback: {
  rating: Number,          // 1–5 stars
  isResolved: Boolean,     // Citizen confirms if resolved
  comment: String,
  submittedAt: Date,
  submittedBy: ObjectId    // User who gave feedback
}
```

If citizen marks `isResolved: false`, the issue status changes to `reopened`.

**Performance Tracking:**
```javascript
resolutionTime: Number,   // Hours from creation to resolution (calculated on save)
penaltyPoints: Number     // Accumulated from escalations (level × 10 points each)
```

**Pre-save Hooks (in order):**
1. **reportId generation** — Finds the highest existing ID, increments by 1, formats as `R#####`
2. **dueTime setting** — Set to `createdAt + 7 days` if not provided
3. **SLA auto-calculation** — Every save recalculates `hoursRemaining` and `isOverdue`; calculates `resolutionTime` when status becomes `resolved`

**Instance Methods:**

- `escalate(reason)` — Increments escalation level (max 3), sets status to `escalated`, records in history, adds penalty points
- `getEscalationTarget()` — Returns who the issue escalates to at each level
- `addUpvote(userId)` — Instance-level upvote (pre-checks duplicate)
- `submitFeedback(rating, comment, isResolved, userId)` — Records citizen feedback

**Static Methods:**

- `Issue.addUpvote(issueId, userId)` — **Atomic** upvote using `findOneAndUpdate` with `$ne` check (prevents race conditions with concurrent upvotes)
- `Issue.removeUpvote(issueId, userId)` — Atomic upvote removal

### 5.3 Notification Model (`models/Notification.js`)

Simple model for in-app notifications.

```javascript
{
  userId: ObjectId,       // Who this notification is for
  message: String,        // Notification text
  type: String,           // e.g., 'status_update', 'assignment'
  isRead: Boolean,
  createdAt: Date
}
```

### 5.4 StateHistory Model (`models/StateHistory.js`)

Records every status change for an issue — creates an audit trail.

```javascript
{
  issueId: ObjectId,
  fromStatus: String,
  toStatus: String,
  changedBy: ObjectId,    // Who made the change
  reason: String,         // Optional reason
  timestamp: Date
}
```

### 5.5 StaffPerformance Model (`models/StaffPerformance.js`)

Tracks individual field officer metrics.

```javascript
{
  staffId: ObjectId,
  totalAssigned: Number,
  totalResolved: Number,
  averageResolutionTime: Number,  // In hours
  overdueCount: Number,
  penaltyPoints: Number,
  period: String,         // e.g., '2024-01' for monthly rollup
  updatedAt: Date
}
```

### 5.6 DepartmentPerformance Model (`models/DepartmentPerformance.js`)

Aggregated department-level metrics:

```javascript
{
  departmentId: String,
  totalIssues: Number,
  resolvedIssues: Number,
  averageResolutionTime: Number,
  slaCompliance: Number,          // Percentage
  citizenSatisfactionScore: Number, // Average rating
  overdueIssues: Number,
  escalationCount: Number,
  period: String
}
```

### 5.7 OTP Model (`models/OTP.js`)

A separate collection for OTP management (alternative to storing OTP on the user):

```javascript
{
  email: String,
  otp: String,           // Hashed OTP
  expiresAt: Date,
  used: Boolean
}
```

---

## Chapter 6: Geography — Wards, Zones & Departments

### 6.1 Overview

CivicPulse models a fictional municipality divided into **16 wards** organized into **2 zones**: North and South. Each ward is **permanently assigned to one department**.

This is the **single source of truth** — defined in `lib/wards.js`. No other file should hardcode ward data.

### 6.2 The Ward Map

```
NORTH ZONE (Wards 1-8)
┌─────────┬────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┐
│ Ward ID │ Ward                       │ Department                  │
├─────────┼────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────┤
│ ward-1  │ Ward 1 — North Zone        │ 🛣️ Roads & Infrastructure    │
│ ward-2  │ Ward 2 — North Zone        │ 💡 Street Lighting          │
│ ward-3  │ Ward 3 — North Zone        │ 🗑️ Waste Management         │
│ ward-4  │ Ward 4 — North Zone        │ 💧 Water & Drainage         │
│ ward-5  │ Ward 5 — North Zone        │ 🌳 Parks & Public Spaces    │
│ ward-6  │ Ward 6 — North Zone        │ 🚦 Traffic & Signage        │
│ ward-7  │ Ward 7 — North Zone        │ 🏥 Public Health & Safety   │
│ ward-8  │ Ward 8 — North Zone        │ 📋 Other / General          │
└─────────┴────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────┘

SOUTH ZONE (Wards 9-16)
┌─────────┬────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┐
│ ward-9  │ Ward 9 — South Zone        │ 🛣️ Roads & Infrastructure    │
│ ward-10 │ Ward 10 — South Zone       │ 💡 Street Lighting          │
│ ward-11 │ Ward 11 — South Zone       │ 🗑️ Waste Management         │
│ ward-12 │ Ward 12 — South Zone       │ 💧 Water & Drainage         │
│ ward-13 │ Ward 13 — South Zone       │ 🌳 Parks & Public Spaces    │
│ ward-14 │ Ward 14 — South Zone       │ 🚦 Traffic & Signage        │
│ ward-15 │ Ward 15 — South Zone       │ 🏥 Public Health & Safety   │
│ ward-16 │ Ward 16 — South Zone       │ 📋 Other / General          │
└─────────┴────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────┘
```

This means every department has **exactly 2 wards** — one in North zone and one in South zone. The Roads department responds to issues in ward-1 (North) and ward-9 (South).

### 6.3 Ward Helper Functions

```javascript
// Get full label: "Ward 3 — North Zone · Waste Management"
getWardLabel('ward-3')

// Get both wards for the Roads department: ['ward-1', 'ward-9']
getDepartmentWards('roads')

// Get all 8 north wards: ['ward-1', 'ward-2', ..., 'ward-8']
getZoneWards('north')

// Get zone from ward: 'north'
getWardZone('ward-3')

// Get department from ward: 'waste'
getWardDepartment('ward-3')

// Find the ward at the intersection of south zone + roads: ward-9
getWardByZoneDept('south', 'roads')
```

### 6.4 Ward Assignments for Users

- **FIELD_OFFICER** — Has a `wardId` (e.g., `ward-3`). They can only see and work on issues in their specific ward.
- **DEPARTMENT_MANAGER** — Has a `departmentId` (e.g., `waste`). They see issues from all wards under their department (ward-3 + ward-11 for Waste Management department).
- **MUNICIPAL_COMMISSIONER / SYSTEM_ADMIN** — No ward/department restriction. Can see all issues.
- **CITIZEN** — No ward assignment. Can report issues in any ward.

### 6.5 The 8 Departments

| Department ID | Display Name | Icon | Issue Category |
|--------------|-------------|------|---------------|
| `roads` | Roads & Infrastructure | 🛣️ | `roads-infrastructure` |
| `lighting` | Street Lighting | 💡 | `street-lighting` |
| `waste` | Waste Management | 🗑️ | `waste-management` |
| `water` | Water & Drainage | 💧 | `water-drainage` |
| `parks` | Parks & Public Spaces | 🌳 | `parks-public-spaces` |
| `traffic` | Traffic & Signage | 🚦 | `traffic-signage` |
| `health` | Public Health & Safety | 🏥 | `public-health-safety` |
| `other` | Other / General | 📋 | `other` |

